1️⃣ Mode / Generation Options
Option	Values / Type	Notes
mode	simple / sadtalker	Determines generation method. simple → MediaPipe talking face, sadtalker → SadTalker pipeline.
stream_mode	complete / chunked / realtime	How the video is returned/streamed.
codec	h264_high / h264_medium / h264_fast / h265_high / webm_high / webm_fast	Used for output video codec.
quality	high / medium / fast	Used for video conversion and optional codec presets.


2️⃣ Text / TTS Options
Option	Type	Default	Notes
prompt	string	"Hello"	Text to speak in the avatar.
tts_engine	string	"espeak"	Which TTS backend to use.
voice	string	"en_female"	Voice selection for TTS.
language	string	"en-US"	Language for TTS.
rate	float	1.0	Speed of speech.
pitch	float	0	Pitch adjustment.
emotion	string	"neutral"	TTS emotion (if supported).
sample_rate	int	16000	Output sample rate for TTS.
format	string	"wav"	Output audio format.


3️⃣ Source Image / Face Options
Option	Type	Default	Notes
image	string / URL / base64 / path	/app/faces/2.jpg	Can be a URL, local path, or base64-encoded image.
still	bool	True	Whether SadTalker should treat image as still (no motion source).
preprocess	string	"crop"	Preprocessing mode for SadTalker input.
resolution	string	"256"	Image resolution for SadTalker.


4️⃣ SadTalker / Video Generation Options
Option	Type	Default	Notes
timeout	int	1200	Maximum generation time in seconds.
enhancer	string	None	Optional image/video enhancer (e.g., gfpgan).
split_chunks	bool	False	Whether to split audio into chunks for generation.
chunk_length	int	10	Seconds per chunk if splitting audio.
fps	int	15	Target frames per second.


5️⃣ Misc / Internal / Debug Options
Option	Type	Notes
benchmark_file	string	Path to benchmark JSON for timeouts / fps.
audio_path	string	Temp file path for TTS output.
video_path	string	Output path for generated video.
/debug/status	endpoint	Returns current system status, available modes, codecs, TTS, disk, memory.
/debug/logs	endpoint	Returns last logs for debugging.
/reload	endpoint	Reload configuration (e.g., default codec).
/health	endpoint	Health check for device + TTS + modes.

✅ Notes / Observations

Your “bring your own image” is already supported via image in JSON.

The TTS options are explicit and separate from the mode options.

Streaming modes (complete, chunked, realtime) are independent of TTS or image inputs.

Some options (timeout, fps, split_chunks) are SadTalker-specific and may be ignored in simple mode.

Debug endpoints expose system state but don’t accept most options—they’re read-only.